### API USAGE GUIDE
### ----------------------------------------------------
### PREREQUISITES:
### 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code.
### 2. Make sure your server is running (`npm run dev` or `npm run start`).
### 3. Replace the `@token` variable below with a valid JWT token. 
###    (For Admin endpoints, make sure the JWT payload has { "role": "ADMIN" })

### Prerequisites Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = YOUR_VALID_JWT_TOKEN
@categoryId = REPLACE_WITH_CATEGORY_ID
@productId = REPLACE_WITH_PRODUCT_ID
@userId = REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID
@companyId = REPLACE_WITH_COMPANY_ID
@orderId = REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID
@customerId = REPLACE_WITH_CUSTOMER_ID
@festivalId = REPLACE_WITH_FESTIVAL_ID
@reviewId = REPLACE_WITH_REVIEW_ID

### ====================================================
### 🔐 AUTH APIs
### ====================================================

### 1. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 2. Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 3. Logout User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 4. Forgot Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 5. Reset Password
# Pass your OTP directly into the body here
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password/YOUR_OTP_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "otp": "123456",
  "password": "NewPassword123"
}

### ====================================================
### 📦 CATEGORY APIs
### ====================================================

### 1. Create Category [ADMIN]
# Requires: name (string, required)
# Response: 201 Created with category object
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Electronics"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 2. List Categories [PUBLIC/USER]
# Supports optional queries: ?page=1&limit=10&search=electro&startDate=2024-01-01&endDate=2024-12-31
# Response: 200 OK with paginated categories array
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories?page=1&limit=10
Content-Type: application/json

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 3. Get Single Category [PUBLIC/USER]
# Requires: valid category ID (24-char hex)
# Response: 200 OK with category object or 404 if not found
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 4. Update Category [ADMIN]
# Requires: valid category ID, optional name
# Response: 200 OK with updated category object
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Home Appliances"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 5. Delete Category (Soft Delete) [ADMIN]
# Requires: valid category ID
# Response: 200 OK with success message
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json


### ====================================================
### 📦 PRODUCT APIs
### ====================================================

### 1. Create Product [ADMIN]
# IMPORTANT: "categories" must be an array of valid Category ObjectId(s).
# "company" is required. "festivals", "price", "stock", "attributes" are optional.
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Samsung Galaxy S24",
  "categories": ["{{categoryId}}"],
  "company": "{{companyId}}",
  "festivals": [],
  "price": 999.99,
  "stock": 50,
  "attributes": {
    "color": "Black",
    "storage": "256GB"
  }
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 2. List Products [PUBLIC/USER]
# Supports optional queries: ?page=1&limit=10&search=samsung&category=ID1,ID2&festivals=ID1,ID2&company=ID&startDate=2024-01-01&endDate=2024-12-31
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?page=1&limit=10
Content-Type: application/json

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 3. Get Single Product [PUBLIC/USER]
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 4. Update Product [ADMIN]
PUT {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra",
  "categories": ["{{categoryId}}"],
  "company": "{{companyId}}",
  "festivals": [],
  "price": 1199.99,
  "stock": 30,
  "attributes": {
    "color": "Black",
    "storage": "512GB"
  }
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 5. Delete Product (Soft Delete) [ADMIN]
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json


### ====================================================
### 🛒 ORDER APIs
### ====================================================

### 1. Create Order [ADMIN]
# Creates a new order with customer and items details
# Required: customerSnapshot (name, phone), items array (product, name, quantity, price, total)
# Optional: customer (customer ID), discount, festival, paymentMethod, paymentStatus
# Response: 201 Created with order object
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer": "{{customerId}}",
  "customerSnapshot": {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "phone": "9876543210"
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "product": "{{productId}}",
      "name": "Samsung Galaxy S24",
      "quantity": 2,
      "price": 999.99,
      "total": 1999.98
    },
    {
      "product": "{{productId}}",
      "name": "Phone Case",
      "quantity": 1,
      "price": 29.99,
      "total": 29.99
    }
  ],
  "subTotal": 2029.97,
  "discount": 50.00,
  "totalAmount": 1979.97,
  "festival": "{{festivalId}}",
  "paymentMethod": "CASH",
  "paymentStatus": "PENDING"
}

### RESPONSE EXAMPLE:
